 <title>Increasing Commitments Bode Well for Future of IoT, AllSeen Alliance</title>
 <link>https://identity.allseenalliance.org/news/blogs/2015/03/increasing-commitments-bode-well-future-iot-allseen-alliance</link>
 <description>
		&lt;span class=&quot;a2a_kit a2a_target addtoany_list&quot; id=&quot;da2a_1&quot;&gt;
			&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_facebook&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_twitter&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_google_plus&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_dd addtoany_share_save&quot; href=&quot;http://www.addtoany.com/share_save#url=https%3A%2F%2Fidentity.allseenalliance.org%2Fnews%2Fblogs%2F2015%2F03%2Fincreasing-commitments-bode-well-future-iot-allseen-alliance&amp;amp;title=Blogs%20-%20AllSeen%20Alliance&quot;&gt; Share&lt;/a&gt;
		&lt;/span&gt;
		&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot;&gt;
&lt;!--//--&gt;&lt;![CDATA[//&gt;&lt;!--
da2a.script_load();
//--&gt;&lt;!]]&gt;
&lt;/script&gt;
		
  &lt;div class=&quot;field-body view-mode-rss&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;As we have worked to build the Internet of Things and deliver its promise of a billion interoperable devices, we’ve learned that success depends on an open framework that gives every product a common language and we’ve learned that building a framework of this scale and impact takes a vibrant and growing community.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At the AllSeen Alliance, you can see this community at work and in full swing: in the ongoing commitment of companies ranging in size from tiny startups to global multinationals, in the incredible collaboration among developers; and in the investment of time and resources towards a common. From the the new and established &lt;a href=&quot;https://allseenalliance.org/about/working-groups&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;workgroups&lt;/a&gt; tackling the challenges of making IoT real to the ever-growing list of  &lt;a href=&quot;https://allseenalliance.org/showcase&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;AllJoyn enabled products hitting the market&lt;/a&gt;, the power of the AllSeen community is palpable.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As IoT technologies mature, we’re seeing some of the worlds leading consumer electronics companies deepen their investments in open source software and collaborative development to accelerate this work and the market opportunities. AllSeen Alliance founding member &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/panasonic-to-share-intellectual-property-to-spur-growth-of-internet-of-things-300053921.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Panasonic today is signaling&lt;/a&gt; a major advancement in its strategy to contribute to and support open source software and collaborative development through the organization.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Speaking today with AllSeen Alliance TSC chair at the &lt;a href=&quot;http://events.linuxfoundation.org/events/embedded-linux-conference&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Embedded Linux Conference&lt;/a&gt; in San Jose, Calif., Panasonic is announcing it will open source its device-to-cloud through the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.opendof.org&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;OpenDOF Project&lt;/a&gt;, in part to contribute new source code in collaboration with the open source community to the AllSeen Alliance’s &lt;a href=&quot;https://wiki.allseenalliance.org/gateway/gatewayagent&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Gateway Working Group&lt;/a&gt;. This work is expected to extend the reach of cloud-based capabilities in AllJoyn through interworking bridges for Echonet devices, security services and proximal networks. This internetworking can help ensure that all devices can benefit from AllJoyn services and can help extend the Alliance’s reach into Asian and European markets.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;To create a global ecosystem of billions of interoperable products, applications and services, groups must not only make their solutions open but also interoperable with others. The AllSeen Alliance, which includes more than 140 members, is committed to creating a simple and open framework that the industry can use within the Internet of Everything technology stack. As a founding member of the AllSeen Alliance and a long-time member of the Linux Foundation, Panasonic shares a deep investment in collaborative development and open source technologies and we applaud the companies moves to this end.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;
</description>
