 <title>In Just One Year... We’ve Come a Long Way</title>
 <link>https://identity.allseenalliance.org/news/blogs/2014/12/just-one-year-we-ve-come-long-way</link>
 <description>
		&lt;span class=&quot;a2a_kit a2a_target addtoany_list&quot; id=&quot;da2a_3&quot;&gt;
			&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_facebook&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_twitter&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_google_plus&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_dd addtoany_share_save&quot; href=&quot;http://www.addtoany.com/share_save#url=https%3A%2F%2Fidentity.allseenalliance.org%2Fnews%2Fblogs%2F2014%2F12%2Fjust-one-year-we-ve-come-long-way&amp;amp;title=Blogs%20-%20AllSeen%20Alliance&quot;&gt; Share&lt;/a&gt;
		&lt;/span&gt;
		
		
  &lt;div class=&quot;field-body view-mode-rss&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;This is a very special week: The AllSeen Alliance is celebrating its &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://allseenalliance.org/announcement/commercial-adoption-major-investments-and-key-technical-contributions-put-allseen&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;one-year anniversary&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and what a tremendous year it has been, far surpassing anything this community could have hoped for when it launched in December 2013.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In just one year, the AllSeen Alliance has grown to &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://allseenalliance.org/announcement/allseen-alliance-reaches-100-companies-committed-advance-internet-everything&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;more than 100 organizations&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;. The initiative has been powerful for everyone who has been a part of it. We’ve been able to work together as companies that are both competitors and collaborators to move a technology and an entire industry forward. That’s no small feat. An open source project shouldn’t invent what doesn’t need to be invented. The innovation lies where we can build upon a technology that we collaboratively created. That’s what AllJoyn provides for IoT. An open platform to enable innovation on top of it.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In just one year, through the power of a shared vision and a commitment to collaborate across industry lines, the AllSeen Alliance, the world’s largest collaborative open source project focused on the Internet of Things, has become the place to solve IoT’s biggest challenges -- interoperability and fragmentation. We have nine Working Groups that are producing code to address critical areas impacting IoT interoperability, including lighting, home automation, security, cloud and analytics. Those include QEO’s data-driven APIs and security enhancements contributed by Technicolor; new lighting service APIs and connected lighting framework from LIFX; a new gateway agent from Affinegy; software update services from Red Bend; analytics from Tellient; and a smart home gateway from Haier; among others.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In just one year, the AllSeen Alliance has augmented and advanced AllJoyn - a software framework powering commercial products today, simple and open technology that connects everything. AllJoyn is an open, universal and secure framework that enables companies to create interoperable products that can discover, connect and interact directly with any other AllJoyn-enabled products. The third release of AllJoyn will be available for download next week.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In just one year, there are dozens of AllJoyn-enabled products in the market, ensuring interoperability among devices in homes and businesses. We’re excited that this roster of products includes Gramofon by Fon, LG televisions, LIFX smart LED light bulbs, Local Motors Rally Fighter, Musaic Wireless HiFi System, Powertech APPSTRIGGER smart socket and Panasonic ALL Series Wireless Speakers, among others. Our &lt;strong&gt;“&lt;a href=&quot;https://allseenalliance.org/certification&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Designed for AllSeen&lt;/a&gt;”&lt;/strong&gt; certification and compliance program was launched earlier this year to ensure consumers receive seamless, out-of-the-box interoperability with AllJoyn-enabled devices.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In just one year, the AllSeen Alliance members and contributors have accomplished so much, but there is still a lot more work to do because the opportunities for IoT are many. The power of the AllSeen Alliance grows from our members. The more voices we can bring to the table, the more we know. The more we know, the more we can get done, the better the results and the greater the innovation. The year ahead holds a lot of excitement and potential for AllJoyn and the future of connected things.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In the year to come, I look forward to seeing more AllJoyn-enabled products come to market and to the realization of an industry transformation born from massive collaboration. Cheers to an innovative 2015!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Philip DesAutels is senior director of IoT at the Linux Foundation and is responsible for managing The AllSeen Alliance collaborative project.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn more about how the AllSeen Alliance is paving the way for IoT interoperability in this &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V_MbMiFI9rQ&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;video from the community&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;
</description>
